{
  "name": "RPlog_Bad_Place_for_a_Call",
  "title": "Bad Place for a Call",
  "summary": "In a recorded holo-message, the careworn New Republic Ambassador Ambrosia Delgard reaches out to the smuggler crew of Andromidas Galaxy Logistics, urging them to abstain from raiding supply convoys in the Caspian system. She explains that the CSA will run a humanitarian relief flotilla -- some ships resembling Imperial vessels -- that must be allowed to pass unmolested, lest the Empire retaliate with Star Destroyers, and offers 30,000 credits as compensation for the crew's enforced inactivity. Much later, the smuggler Jaspar returns the call from the back room of a seedy Nar Shaddaa nightclub, agreeing to the terms while a furious Gamorrean pounds on the locked door demanding he hurry to place a swoop-race bet. Just as Jaspar signs off, the Gamorrean bursts in, grabs him by the neck, and slams his face into the terminal, cutting the connection.",
